    "Body": " QA TESTER Rec Room - 2.9 Seattle, WA Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $60,000 - $83,000 a year Benefits Health Insurance Unlimited Paid Time Off Retirement Plan Vision Insurance Dental Insurance Qualifications Writing Skills Communication Skills Unity UI Jira Full Job Description Rec Room is a cross-platform social playground with a growing community of users from all around the world. Our mission is to ensure that Rec Room is a fun and welcoming environment for people from all walks of life. An app of this size and complexity needs constant testing. That's where you come in! IN THIS ROLE YOU WILL: Spend the bulk of your time in Rec Room, using a variety of a variety of traditional screen-based devices and VR headsets. You will become a deep expert on all things Rec Room! Ensure that bug database is always up-to-date with high-quality bug reports and test passes Work closely with the entire Rec Room team to understand and reproduce bugs during the development of new features Work closely with the entire Rec Room team to develop test plans As needed work on special events (i.e., trailer shoots, community town halls, etc.) You will be a bug hunter, puzzling out why a particular issue is happening and spending time in multiplayer sessions with Rec Room Community members. Work directly with the Rec Room community forums to ingest, filter and consolidate community reported issues To apply please submit cover letter with the statement \"I understand that this is a full-time testing role, and not an immediate stepping stone to a design/art/engineering job\" with your application REQUIREMENTS: 2+ Years' Experience as a software tester; ideally working on a live service Experience writing and executing test plans Experience with Jira or similar bug tracking tool Proven ability to write high-quality repro steps A methodical and detail-oriented work style Excellent ability to solve problems, critically think, and apply logic in a fast-paced, ambiguous environment. Excellent written and verbal communication skills Ability to relocate to Seattle, WA (Remote work until the WA State stay home order is lifted) Submit cover letter with your full name and the statement \"I understand that this is a full-time testing role, and not an immediate stepping stone to a design/art/engineering job\" with your application BONUS POINTS Experience testing multiplayer video games Experience testing cross-platform games Familiar with online communities in the games space (i.e. Steam, Reddit, Discord, Twitter, specific game forums, etc.) Familiarity with the Unity game engine (even as a hobbyist, just know your way around the UI) Experience with VR devices generally Experience with UGC games Experience or interest in game development Experience with Rec Room specifically COMPANY INFO TO KNOW Rec Room offers generous medical, dental, and vision plans that cover you, your spouse/domestic partner, and children. We also support your retirement benefits with a company match. Rec Room values work-life balance by providing unlimited paid time off. Our company values are real and drive our culture. We work hard to be a safe and friendly place for people from all walks of life. Rec Room provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws. "
